Male postabdomen: Sternite 5 longer than wide, narrowed posteriorly with posterior corners produced as thin curved lobes, anterior apodeme short, slightly narrower than external portion (
Fig. 45
). Surstylus narrow, not strongly scooped. Pregonite small but distinct. Postgonite with lobes narrowly separated, both pointed, anterior lobe broader. Basiphallus with short, broad epiphallus, slightly longer, narrow preepiphallus. Distiphallus with short, smooth dorsal tube, ventral point projecting (
Fig. 42
).
